label.value: decreased glutamate import during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of glutamate into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of glutamine into the cell is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of glutamine into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of glycine into the cell is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of glycine into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of threonine into the cell is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of threonine into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of tyrosine into the cell is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of tyrosine into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: increased duration of mitotic cell cycle phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of one or more mitotic cell cycle phases is longer than normal.

label.value: decreased duration of mitotic cell cycle phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of one or more mitotic cell cycle phases is shorter than normal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transport is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which myo-inositol import into the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of myo-inositol into the cell is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of myo-inositol into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing papulacandin B.

label.value: normal level of substance in cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a polysaccharide measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of beta-D-glucan measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of galactomannan measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased polysaccharide level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a polysaccharide measured in a cell is lower than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of alpha-D-glucan measured in the cell wall is lower than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of beta-D-glucan measured in the cell wall is lower than normal.

label.value: increased polysaccharide level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a polysaccharide measured in a cell is greater than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of alpha-D-glucan measured in the cell wall is greater than normal.

label.value: altered polysaccharide level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a polysaccharide measured in a cell differs from normal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a glucosyltransferase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a glucosyltransferase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a glucosyltransferase activity is decreased.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a glucosyltransferase activity is increased.

label.value: resistance to heat shock during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show decreased sensitivity to heat shock. Heat shock is a form of heat stress in which cells are briefly exposed to a very high temperature.

label.value: normal cellular response to heat shock

value.value: A cellular response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cellular response to heat shock is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Heat shock is a form of heat stress in which cells are briefly exposed to a very high temperature.
A phenotype that affects the binding of a gene product to another substance. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene, and may normally bind DNA, protein, or both in chromatin.

A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of DNA binding at a replication origin by a gene product is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The relevant gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

A molecular function phenotype in which DNA binding at a replication origin by a gene product does not occur, when a gene or the bound DNA sequence is mutated. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: normal RNA level during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell that is subject to nitrogen starvation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to amitrole. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of amitrole that allows wild type cells to grow.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to 4-nitroquinoline N-oxide. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of 4-nitroquinoline N-oxide that allows wild type cells to grow.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing carbonyl cyanide m-chlorophenyl hydrazone (CCCP).
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing Gentian violet (also known as crystal violet).

label.value: decreased protein level during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein level during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide is higher than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of hydrogen peroxide than normal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of catalase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which catalase activity is absent.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutathione-disulfide reductase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutathione-disulfide reductase activity is decreased.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutathione-disulfide reductase activity is increased.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of menadione than normal.
